;\"><a style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>&nbsp;from 1990 he listed<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0b0080; background: none;\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>&nbsp;\"some of the many areas in which hypertext is used\" and put an encyclopedia first.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'html, alaa', '', 'published', 0);
